Hello?

12:21.273 --> 12:24.401
- Hello?
- Hello, Sidney.

12:24.484 --> 12:28.321
- Yes?
- What's your favorite scary movie?

12:28.405 --> 12:32.242
- Who is this?
- You tell me.

12:33.994 --> 12:38.665
Cory Gillis,
555-0176.

12:38.748 --> 12:40.792
- Oh, shit!
- Hot flash, Cory-

12:40.876 --> 12:42.794
- Shit!
- Crank calls are a criminal offense...

12:42.878 --> 12:45.171
prosecuted under
penal code 653-M.

12:47.257 --> 12:49.175
Hope you enjoyed
the movie.

12:49.259 --> 12:51.344
Time to change
numbers again?

12:51.428 --> 12:53.346
No. It'll die off.

12:53.430 --> 12:55.473
It's opening weekend.
We'll see how it goes.

12:55.557 --> 12:57.475
Okay.

12:58.977 --> 13:00.937
You know, Ron, uh,

13:00.979 --> 13:03.940
it's not an easy thing to be accused
of a crime you didn't commit,

13:03.982 --> 13:07.444
particularly one
as heinous as murder.

13:07.485 --> 13:09.446
But how do people treat you
now that they know the truth...

13:09.487 --> 13:11.448
- about your innocence?
- Most people are cool.

13:11.489 --> 13:14.451
There's some who still keep
a safe distance, which is odd for me,

13:14.492 --> 13:16.703
'cause I've always been
sort of a people person.

13:16.786 --> 13:19.206
But you were
wrongly accused!

13:19.289 --> 13:21.208
You were fully exonerated.

13:21.291 --> 13:22.959
Yeah, well, that and a nickel
will get you a cup of coffee.

13:23.043 --> 13:25.629
- Even that's not true anymore.

13:25.712 --> 13:27.714
Well, certainly, with Gale Weathers'
book- and now the movie-

13:27.797 --> 13:31.551
- it's set the record straight for Cotton Weary.
- One would think.

13:31.635 --> 13:33.386
But, uh, Gale's-
Gale's been terrific.

13:33.470 --> 13:35.972
Hey! Move your ass, okay?
You're late.

13:36.014 --> 13:40.352
Don't forget about the martini mixer
tonight at the Delta Lambda Zetas.

13:40.435 --> 13:43.813
- I don't think I'm going to be able to make it, Hal.
- What?

13:43.855 --> 13:46.858
Don't even try to bag, okay?
'Cause you promised me.

13:46.942 --> 13:50.237
- A vague promise at best.
- Nobody's asking you to join, okay?

13:50.320 --> 13:52.405
It's a party.
Free beer, meet the girls.

13:52.489 --> 13:54.407
Hallie, you know me
and organized religion.

13:54.491 --> 13:56.826
- It's a sorority.
- Worse.

13:56.868 --> 14:00.205
Look, Sid, just lower the walls
for the next few days.

14:00.247 --> 14:03.542
This self-induced isolation
you got goin' is not healthy.

14:03.583 --> 14:06.086
- I'm fine.
- "I'm fine."

14:06.169 --> 14:10.215
Yes, I know. "I'm fine" is stretched
tightly across your face.

14:10.298 --> 14:12.217
Check out the news.

14:17.222 --> 14:19.432
The two Windsor College
students were murdered...

14:19.516 --> 14:23.186
last night during a sneak preview
of the new movie Stab.

14:23.270 --> 14:26.773
Police haven't released any information
except for the victims' names,

14:26.856 --> 14:29.818
but a press conference is scheduled
for later today.

14:29.901 --> 14:32.821
The victims, Maureen Evans
and Phil Stevens,

14:32.904 --> 14:34.823
were both Windsor seniors.

14:34.906 --> 14:38.368
- Where's Randy?
- He's got Film Theory this morning.

14:38.410 --> 14:40.453
...ended with the brutal murders
of two promising-

14:50.046 --> 14:52.132
Sidney! Sidney!

14:52.215 --> 14:54.134
Sidney, did you know
the victims?

14:54.217 --> 14:56.136
- Do you feel threatened by the murders?
- No comment.

14:56.219 --> 14:58.138
- Do you think there'll be more murders?
- Sidney! Sidney!

14:58.221 --> 15:00.432
- What can you tell us about the victims?
- How about the police?

15:00.515 --> 15:03.351
- We just need one statement.
- Please talk to us!

15:03.435 --> 15:06.813
You could say what happened in that
theater is a result of the movie itself.

15:06.897 --> 15:10.984
That is so Moral Majority. You can't
blame real violence on entertainment.

15:11.067 --> 15:14.446
What? Wait a second. Yes, you can.
Don't you even watch the news?

15:14.487 --> 15:16.948
Yeah. Hello! The murderer was wearing
a ghost mask, okay?

15:16.990 --> 15:19.326
Just like in the movie.
It's directly responsible.

15:19.409 --> 15:22.120
No, it's not. Movies are not responsible
for our actions.

15:22.204 --> 15:26.249
It's a classic case of life
imitating art imitating life.

15:26.291 --> 15:28.710
This is not a hypothetical.
It's not about art.

15:28.793 --> 15:31.421
I had Biology with that girl.
This is reality.

15:31.463 --> 15:35.258
Thank you. I agree with you.
Let me tell you about reality, Mickey.

15:35.300 --> 15:37.260
I lived through this.
Okay?

15:37.302 --> 15:39.429
Life is life.
It doesn't imitate anything.

15:39.512 --> 15:41.806
Come on, Randy,
with all due respect,

15:41.890 --> 15:44.517
the killer obviously patterned himself
after two serial killers...

15:44.601 --> 15:47.729
- who have been immortalized on film.
- Thank you.

15:47.812 --> 15:50.232
Are you suggesting that someone's trying
to make a real-life sequel?

15:50.315 --> 15:54.069
Stab 2? Who'd want to do that?
Sequels suck.

15:54.152 --> 15:56.071
- Oh, please. Please!

15:56.154 --> 15:59.282
- By definition alone, they're inferior films.
- Bullshit generalization.

15:59.324 --> 16:01.451
Many sequels have
surpassed their original.

16:01.535 --> 16:03.995
- Oh, yeah?
- Name one.

16:04.037 --> 16:05.580
Aliens. Far better
than the first.

16:05.664 --> 16:07.541
Yeah, well, there's
no accounting for taste.

16:07.624 --> 16:09.793
Thank you. Ridley Scott rules.
Name another.

16:09.834 --> 16:14.214
No. Aliens is a classic, okay?
"Get away from her, you bitch!"

16:14.297 --> 16:16.967
Believe the line is "Stay away from her,
you bitch. " It's film class, right?

16:19.052 --> 16:21.137
- Whatever. You know what I mean.
- Another.

16:21.179 --> 16:22.722
- T2.
- Mmm.

16:22.806 --> 16:24.516
You've got a hard-on
for Cameron.

16:24.599 --> 16:26.643
- Big one.
- Wait a second.

16:26.685 --> 16:29.563
- The first Terminator is historical.
- Yeah.

16:29.646 --> 16:32.566
"Sarah Connor?"
"Yes."

16:32.649 --> 16:34.568
- All right. All right, okay.

16:34.651 --> 16:36.945
House Il:
The Second Story.

16:37.028 --> 16:42.576
- What?
- The entire horror genre was destroyed by sequels.

16:42.659 --> 16:44.953
Hey, I got it, by the way.
I got it.

16:45.036 --> 16:47.122
The Godfather, Part II.

16:51.042 --> 16:53.712
Very good.
That's the Oscar-winning exception.

16:53.795 --> 16:56.840
- All right, that's enough.

16:56.923 --> 17:02.387
That'll be a wrap. The sequel discussion
to be continued.

17:04.890 --> 17:08.059
So, Mr. Originality, how would
you make it different?

17:08.143 --> 17:10.561
I'd let the geek
get the girl.

17:16.151 --> 17:18.069
Three hundred people watched.
Nobody did anything.

17:18.153 --> 17:20.405
They thought it was a publicity stunt,
for Christ's sakes.

17:20.488 --> 17:22.449
And it would have been a good one too.

17:22.531 --> 17:24.451
- It's starting again, Randy.
- It's not.

17:24.534 --> 17:27.746
Shit happens at the movies. People
get robbed, shot, maimed, murdered.

17:27.829 --> 17:30.749
Multiplex is just a very dangerous place
to be these days.

17:30.790 --> 17:32.959
Yeah, and you are
in extreme denial.

17:33.043 --> 17:35.629
And you should be too.
This has nothing to do with us.

17:35.712 --> 17:37.631
Randy, a guy in a ghost mask
hacked up two people...

17:37.714 --> 17:40.342
in a movie theater
telling our life story.

17:40.425 --> 17:44.179
- Coincidence?
- You know what happened at Woodsboro.

17:44.262 --> 17:47.682
- You can't ignore it.
- I know, Sid, but I don't want to go back there again.

17:47.766 --> 17:50.227
Can't we just go back to our
pseudo-quasi-happy existence?

17:50.268 --> 17:53.855
- Hello, Derek. How ya doin'?
- Hey, Sid.

17:53.939 --> 17:56.274
- I heard. You weren't in class.
- Yeah, I know.

17:56.316 --> 17:58.985
I skipped. I couldn't take all
the "that's her" looks.

17:59.069 --> 18:00.987
Is there anything
I can do?

18:01.071 --> 18:02.989
Well, you got any tricks
for getting me back...

18:03.073 --> 18:05.867
to a pseudo-quasi-
happy existence?

18:05.951 --> 18:08.954
- I might just have one for that.
- Yeah?

18:09.037 --> 18:10.956
Oh, yeah?
What is it?

18:16.628 --> 18:18.588
That was pretty good.

18:20.382 --> 18:22.300
Get a room.

18:32.310 --> 18:35.188
They're threatening to what?
Are you kidding me?

18:35.272 --> 18:38.066
They'd be stupid
to pull this movie.

18:38.149 --> 18:41.278
With all this free press, they're
gonna have huge numbers this weekend.

18:41.361 --> 18:43.488
It'll break
box office records.

18:43.572 --> 18:46.908
- Consider it done.

18:46.992 --> 18:48.910
Uh, Miss Weathers?
Hi. I'm Joel.

18:48.994 --> 18:51.121
The affiliate sent me.
I'm your new cameraman.

18:51.204 --> 18:53.164
- Yeah. You got experience?
- Huh? Uh, yeah.

18:53.206 --> 18:55.542
I mean, I'm local,
but I shot the bingo finals.

18:55.625 --> 18:57.544
- Great. Great.
- I almost got an award for that.

18:57.627 --> 18:59.546
All right, listen, Joel.
This is how it works.

18:59.629 --> 19:01.548
I point, you shoot.

19:01.631 --> 19:03.884
You stay focussed and fast on your feet,
and we'll get along fine.

19:03.967 --> 19:05.886
You're playing with the big boys now,
you got it?

19:05.969 --> 19:07.888
Got it! Got you covered.
I'm all over it.

19:07.971 --> 19:09.890
Don't worry about a thing.
How hard can it be?

19:09.973 --> 19:11.892
You point and I shoot.
I'm there!

19:11.975 --> 19:13.977
Excuse me, Miss Weathers?
Uh, could I have a minute?

19:14.060 --> 19:16.146
- No.
- Just one second.

19:16.229 --> 19:18.148
I- I know you probably
get this all the time,

19:18.190 --> 19:20.150
but I just wanted to say
I am such a big fan of your work.

19:20.192 --> 19:22.569
I just finished you book.
I- I couldn't put it down.

19:22.652 --> 19:25.906
Insightful, probing-
I just really, really loved your book.

19:25.989 --> 19:28.867
- Thank you. Thanks.
- Sure.

19:28.950 --> 19:30.869
I'm a writer myself.

19:30.952 --> 19:32.871
I write for the local paper,
for the Post Telegram.

19:32.954 --> 19:36.875
I'm Debbie Salt. I took your seminar
in Chicago last year.

19:36.917 --> 19:40.086
I was the one in the front row asking
all the questions.

19:40.170 --> 19:42.839
- Right. I thought you looked familiar.
- Oh, thank you.

19:42.923 --> 19:44.925
Um, can't wait
to see the movie.

19:45.008 --> 19:47.052
You know, you must be getting
quite a lot of flak on that, right?

19:47.135 --> 19:49.679
I mean, with all the
violence-in-cinema issues.

19:49.763 --> 19:51.932
What is your position
going to be?

19:52.015 --> 19:53.934
- No comment.
- Miss Weathers, please- I would-

19:54.017 --> 19:56.770
It would be an honor for me if I could
just get a quote from you for my story.

19:56.853 --> 19:58.772
Okay. Begin quote:

19:58.855 --> 20:01.566
- Great.
- "Your flattering remarks are both desperate and obvious."

20:01.650 --> 20:03.568
- Ouch!
- End quote.

20:03.652 --> 20:06.571
Gale, what are you doing here? Do you think
these murders are connected to Sidney Prescott?

20:06.655 --> 20:08.573
Miss Weathers, what's your theory
on these murders?

20:08.657 --> 20:10.575
What's your feeling
about this?

20:10.659 --> 20:12.619
May I have your attention.

20:12.702 --> 20:15.705
- My name is Chief Louis Hartley-
- Chief Hartley.

20:15.789 --> 20:19.584
Hi. Gale Weathers,
author of The Woodsboro Murders.

20:19.668 --> 20:21.711
Do you think the killer
will strike again?

20:21.753 --> 20:25.173
We have no evidence
that this is a serial killer.

20:25.257 --> 20:27.175
- I'd like to read from a prepared-
- Can you tell us of any...

20:27.259 --> 20:29.344
precautions
that you're taking?

20:29.427 --> 20:32.847
Well, first of all, we think it's just
an isolated incident,

20:32.931 --> 20:36.476
- and we will be-
- Ladies.

20:36.560 --> 20:38.478
Oh, my God.
This is huge.

20:38.562 --> 20:40.647
Do you have
any suspects?

20:40.730 --> 20:43.316
- Sidney, look. It's Gale Weathers.
- What?

20:43.400 --> 20:45.360
Star of the Gale Weathers
press conference,

20:45.443 --> 20:47.362
based on the book
by Gale Weathers.

20:47.445 --> 20:50.490
Soon to be a major motion picture
starring Gale Weathers.

20:50.574 --> 20:54.119
- Be kind. She saved our lives.
- She had calf implants.

20:54.202 --> 20:57.122
Chief Hartley, do you plan
on giving the town a curfew?

20:57.163 --> 20:59.124
I'm gonna get closer.

21:00.792 --> 21:04.671
- So that's her?
- Yeah.

21:08.049 --> 21:09.968
Hello, girls.
Enjoying yourselves?

21:10.051 --> 21:12.971
- Hello, Sister Lois, Sister Murphy.
- Hello, pledge. Hi, Sidney.

21:13.013 --> 21:17.350
- Hey.
- This must be flat-out hell for you.

21:17.434 --> 21:20.687
- How are you holding up?
- I manage.

21:20.770 --> 21:24.149
It's really weird, isn't it? To think
this fuss is all because of you!

21:24.191 --> 21:28.445
I mean, not directly, but in some
six-degrees-of-Kevin Bacon way.

21:28.486 --> 21:33.742
Hallie, are you gonna bring your friend
to our little martini mixer tonight?

21:33.825 --> 21:37.245
- I have a lot of work to do.
- We'll be there.

21:37.329 --> 21:40.248
Oh, good. Because Sid,
we have our eyes on you.

21:40.332 --> 21:42.667
You hang in there, and if there's
anything we can do-

21:42.751 --> 21:46.254
The Delta Lambdas are very sensitive
to your plight.

21:46.338 --> 21:48.548
- Yeah. Bye!
- Bye!

21:50.467 --> 21:54.387
- You gonna start to dress like that once you get in?
- That's not gonna happen.

21:54.471 --> 21:57.474
The Delta Lambdas are the biggest
bunch of fuckin'-

21:57.557 --> 22:00.310
Hey! I'm pledging
Delta Lambda, thank you.

22:02.354 --> 22:04.731
Oh, my God.

22:07.359 --> 22:09.319
Who's that?

22:11.363 --> 22:13.281
Dewey?

22:13.365 --> 22:16.826
Hey!

22:16.910 --> 22:20.205
- What are you doing here?
- Ah!

22:20.247 --> 22:23.083
- Oh, I was worried about you.
- Yeah?

22:23.166 --> 22:25.252
I heard about what happened
and I was on the next plane.

22:25.335 --> 22:27.254
- Oh.
- Can we talk?

22:27.337 --> 22:29.256
Yeah. Yeah.

22:30.340 --> 22:32.259
Are you okay?

22:32.342 --> 22:36.096
I'm fine, Dewey,
or I was.

22:36.179 --> 22:39.933
I mean, things were okay
until now.

22:40.016 --> 22:43.061
But, uh,
theater's going great.

22:43.144 --> 22:46.356
I got my first starring role.
We open in two days.

22:46.398 --> 22:48.650
- That is great.
- Yeah. I'm loving it.

22:48.733 --> 22:50.652
You know, and I've got
some great friends,

22:50.735 --> 22:54.239
and, uh,
I'm seeing someone.

22:54.322 --> 22:58.368
Nice guy. Premed,
no apparent psychotic tendencies.

23:00.245 --> 23:02.205
I was just worried.

23:02.247 --> 23:08.128
Look, Sid, if there is some
freaked-out psycho trying to follow...

23:08.211 --> 23:11.715
in Billy Loomis's footsteps,
you probably already know him.

23:11.756 --> 23:15.218
Or her, or them.

23:15.302 --> 23:18.179
They're probably
already in your life.

23:18.263 --> 23:21.808
They get off on that.

23:21.892 --> 23:24.728
I just want you
to be careful, Sid.

23:28.440 --> 23:33.278
Oh, you- You think I don't
know that, Dewey?

23:33.361 --> 23:36.489
But what am I
supposed to do?

23:36.573 --> 23:40.869
Just cut everybody off?
Crawl under a rock? What?

23:44.122 --> 23:48.585
Just watch out.
Keep an eye out.

23:48.668 --> 23:51.922
I'm gonna talk to Chief Hartley
and the local police.

23:52.005 --> 23:55.091
I'm gonna
just hang around.

23:55.133 --> 23:59.012
I wanna make sure you're safe,
if that's all right with you.

23:59.095 --> 24:01.014
Yeah.
I'd be honored.

24:04.017 --> 24:06.353
All right, Sid.

24:14.945 --> 24:19.199
Hey.

24:19.282 --> 24:21.201
- You okay?
- Uh-huh.

24:21.284 --> 24:23.203
- Who was that guy?
- An old friend.

24:23.286 --> 24:25.580
Deputy Dewey, Woodsboro's finest.
What's he doing here?

24:25.664 --> 24:28.583
He's worried.
Our surrogate big brother.

24:28.667 --> 24:31.419
Nothing like a funeral to bring
the family together.

24:31.503 --> 24:34.005
I'm gonna go say hi.

24:34.089 --> 24:38.051
- Chief Hartley said the girl
was stabbed seven- - Drop it.

24:38.134 --> 24:40.053
Hello, Sidney.

24:40.136 --> 24:43.807
- How are you?
- Hi. What do you want, Gale?

24:43.848 --> 24:47.394
Well, I was hoping I might get
just a few words with you.

24:49.896 --> 24:53.149
- Cotton.
- Hi, Sidney.

24:53.191 --> 24:55.485
Here we are at Windsor College,
where Sidney Prescott...

24:55.527 --> 24:58.238
has just been reunited with Cotton Weary
for the first time...

24:58.321 --> 25:00.824
since she wrongly accused
him of murdering her mother.

25:00.866 --> 25:03.743
- What the hell are you doing?
- We want to know how you feel.

25:03.827 --> 25:06.454
Tell us everything that's happened,
looking back on the last two years.

25:06.538 --> 25:09.916
Sidney, I'd just like to say
that I forgive and forget,

25:10.000 --> 25:13.086
and just like you, I'd like to get
back on with my own life.

25:13.169 --> 25:15.714
- Do you have any comments?
- You bitch!

25:15.797 --> 25:17.924
- Ah-ah.
- Deep breaths. Lot of deep breaths.

25:18.008 --> 25:20.677
Oh, Sidney,
share with us, please!

25:20.760 --> 25:23.013
- I'll share with you!
- Okay, okay, okay.

25:23.096 --> 25:25.056
Did you get that
on film?

25:25.098 --> 25:26.892
Yes, I got that
on film.

25:26.975 --> 25:29.227
Sid? Wait, wait, wait,
wait, wait.

25:29.311 --> 25:31.855
Where's she going, Gale?
Sidney?

25:31.897 --> 25:34.024
Where's she going?

25:34.065 --> 25:36.026
Gale, I-I thought we had
an official interview.

25:36.067 --> 25:38.278
What's going on?
She didn't know?

25:38.361 --> 25:42.407
- Man, that was cold.
- Hey, you need to check your conscience at the door, sweetie.

25:42.490 --> 25:44.409
I'm not here
to be loved.

25:44.492 --> 25:46.411
Gale, you promised me ten minutes
of national coverage.

25:46.494 --> 25:48.413
You'll get
your ten minutes...

25:48.496 --> 25:51.541
when I get
my goddamn interview.

25:51.625 --> 25:53.960
Don't walk away from me, Gale.
I'm still-

25:54.044 --> 25:56.504
Gale, I did my part!

25:56.588 --> 25:58.506
Joel!

26:03.553 --> 26:06.097
Dewey.

26:06.181 --> 26:08.099
What are you
doing here?

26:08.183 --> 26:10.310
Why don't you just
leave her alone?

26:10.393 --> 26:12.521
Hasn't she been
through enough?

26:12.604 --> 26:16.066
And my name is Dwight.

26:16.149 --> 26:19.486
I was just doing my job,
Dwight.

26:19.569 --> 26:23.240
- No matter who gets hurt in the process?
- Hey!

26:23.281 --> 26:25.492
Who got punched here-
again?

26:25.575 --> 26:29.246
Well, I don't condone violence,
but maybe you deserved it.

26:29.287 --> 26:33.208
Page 32: "Deputy Dewey
filled the room...

26:33.291 --> 26:35.460
with his Barney Fife-ish
presence."

26:35.544 --> 26:37.879
You read my book.

26:37.963 --> 26:40.048
Oh, yes, I do read,
Miss Weathers.

26:40.131 --> 26:43.093
Oh, Dewey, don't take it so seriously.
It's a character in a book.

26:43.134 --> 26:46.846
Page 41:

26:46.930 --> 26:50.976
"Deputy Dewey oozed
with inexperience."

26:52.811 --> 26:55.313
Don't you think you're overreacting
just a little bit?

26:55.355 --> 27:00.986
No. What I think is that you're a money-hungry,
fame-seeking- and forgive me for saying-

27:01.069 --> 27:05.240
mediocre writer who's got a cold storage
shed where her heart should be.

27:05.323 --> 27:07.450
No offense intended.

27:07.492 --> 27:09.452
Dewey, I never meant
to imply-

27:09.494 --> 27:11.580
How do you know that my
dimwitted inexperience isn't...

27:11.663 --> 27:15.375
merely a subtle form of manipulation
used to lower people's expectations,

27:15.458 --> 27:20.672
enhancing my ability to effectively
maneuver within any given situation?

27:28.972 --> 27:31.808
I'm sorry.

27:33.894 --> 27:36.229
I don't know
what else to say...

27:36.313 --> 27:39.482
except I'm sorry.

27:39.566 --> 27:43.153
No. I'm the one
that's sorry.

27:43.195 --> 27:45.322
I misjudged you.

27:45.405 --> 27:48.074
Now, if you'll
excuse me,

27:48.158 --> 27:50.744
I have some oozing to do.

27:52.370 --> 27:54.915
One more thing.

27:54.998 --> 27:56.917
Nice streaks.

27:59.169 --> 28:01.087
Well.

28:12.891 --> 28:14.851
Hey, I am not
a sorority pusher.

28:14.893 --> 28:16.853
I just think,
despite its trivialities,

28:16.895 --> 28:21.274
it is a life-affirming, mentally stable,
healthy environment for you.

28:21.358 --> 28:24.277
I mean,
look at this place.

28:24.361 --> 28:27.239
I think you're taking your psych major
a little too seriously, Hallie.

28:27.322 --> 28:29.533
I'm fine.

28:29.574 --> 28:32.160
Yeah? That's beginning
to become your theme song.

28:32.244 --> 28:35.622
"I'm fine." Yeah- Fucked up,
insecure, neurotic and emotional.

28:35.705 --> 28:37.749
Sidney, you made it!

28:37.832 --> 28:40.794
Hi!
No, I really mean that.

28:40.877 --> 28:42.796
- Hi.
- Hi.

28:42.879 --> 28:44.881
Do you girls
want a drink?

28:44.923 --> 28:49.761
Uh, well, actually, yeah, but
you know what? We'll get it ourselves.

28:57.727 --> 29:01.439
I love those guys.
Are they still together?

29:01.523 --> 29:03.441
I haven't seen it
in, like, three weeks.

29:03.525 --> 29:05.443
- No, they broke up again.
- Really?

29:05.527 --> 29:07.445
Mm-hmm. Sarah found out
that Bailey slept with Gwen.

29:07.529 --> 29:09.489
She dumped him, like,
two episodes ago.

29:09.573 --> 29:11.491
I wish she'd get
her shit together.

29:11.575 --> 29:14.536
- Hold on. Someone's calling.

29:14.619 --> 29:16.538
Omega Beta Zeta.

29:16.621 --> 29:18.540
Hello?

29:18.623 --> 29:21.251
- Yes?
- Who is this?

29:21.293 --> 29:24.296
- Cici. Who's this?
- Who do you think?

29:24.337 --> 29:26.798
Ted?
Where are you?

29:26.840 --> 29:29.593
Are you drinking?
Hold on.

29:29.676 --> 29:33.346
Ted's on the other line.
He sounds drunk. I'll call you back.

29:33.430 --> 29:35.515
That shit only calls you
when he's drunk.

29:35.599 --> 29:38.518
- Don't go over there, Cici.
- All right. I'll call you back.

29:41.897 --> 29:44.441
Okay, Ted. You sound loaded.
What's up?

29:44.524 --> 29:46.484
Who's Ted?

29:46.526 --> 29:49.029
Oh, I'm sorry.
My bad.

29:49.112 --> 29:51.031
I thought you were
someone else.

29:51.114 --> 29:53.033
That's okay.
I am.

29:53.116 --> 29:55.577
Who are you calling for?
Nobody's here.

29:55.660 --> 29:57.579
Where is everybody?

29:57.662 --> 30:00.916
We're cosponsoring the acid rain mixer
at Phi Gamma Alpha tonight.

30:00.999 --> 30:03.835
- Why aren't you there?
- I'm "sober sister."

30:03.919 --> 30:06.588
I need to be here in case
a drunk sister calls and needs a ride.

30:06.671 --> 30:10.008
- That's too bad.
- "Drink with your brain." That's our motto.

30:10.050 --> 30:13.011
- Who are you calling for?
- What if I said you?

30:13.094 --> 30:16.306
What if I said good-bye?

30:16.348 --> 30:18.475
Why would you
want to do that?

30:20.185 --> 30:24.147
- Why do you always answer a question with a question?
- I'm inquisitive.

30:24.189 --> 30:29.069
Yeah, and I'm impatient. Do you want
to leave a message for someone?

30:29.152 --> 30:32.239
Do you want to die
tonight, Cici?

30:38.703 --> 30:40.747
Omega Beta Zeta.

30:40.830 --> 30:42.749
So, was it Teddy?

30:42.832 --> 30:45.544
No. It was some creep asshole
trying to scare me.

30:45.627 --> 30:47.921
That movie Stab is
bringing out the crazies.

30:50.590 --> 30:53.260
- Shit.
- What is it?

30:53.343 --> 30:55.303
- I heard a noise.
- Where?

30:55.387 --> 30:57.347
Upstairs.

30:57.389 --> 31:00.600
- Shit!

31:02.978 --> 31:07.190
- Hello? Hello?
- Kill, kill, kill, kill, kill, kill.

31:07.274 --> 31:09.317
- Die, die, die, die, die. - Stop it!

31:09.401 --> 31:11.862
I can't believe you're alone
in that house.

31:11.903 --> 31:13.864
- I don't think I'm alone.

31:15.282 --> 31:17.242
I'm out of here.

31:23.748 --> 31:26.084
You're breaking up.
Where are you?

31:26.126 --> 31:28.879
- Outside.
- Don't panic, Cici.

31:28.962 --> 31:31.882
- Call campus security.
- Okay.

31:37.262 --> 31:39.848
Campus Security.

31:39.931 --> 31:42.767
- Hi. I'm calling from the Omega Beta-
- I can't hear you. Hello?

31:42.851 --> 31:45.061
Hello?

31:45.103 --> 31:47.731
- Can you hear me now?
- Hello?

31:47.772 --> 31:49.983
- Hello? Shit!

31:54.821 --> 31:56.781
- Campus Security.
- Yes. I'm calling from-

31:56.823 --> 31:58.909
I can't hear you.
Hello?

31:58.950 --> 32:02.162
- I'm calling from Omega Beta Zeta house.

32:02.245 --> 32:04.164
Look, someone
is harassing me.

32:04.247 --> 32:06.166
- Hello? Shit!

32:06.249 --> 32:08.168
- Hey!

32:08.251 --> 32:10.420
- Jesus, Dawnie, you scared me.
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

32:10.503 --> 32:12.464
Did anyone call for me?

32:12.505 --> 32:16.092
- What are you doing here?
- I live here, remember?

32:16.134 --> 32:18.428
I just thought you were
going to the mixer.

32:18.470 --> 32:21.389
Yeah, I am. I had to change,
so I'll be out of here now.

32:24.809 --> 32:26.853
Omega Beta Zeta.

32:26.937 --> 32:29.439
- Is Cici there?
- Mm-hmm. Who's calling?

32:29.523 --> 32:33.401
- It's Ted.
- It's your ill-conceived boyfriend.

32:33.485 --> 32:35.570
Okay, so, I'll
see you later.

32:35.654 --> 32:39.032
And don't forget
to set the alarm.

32:39.115 --> 32:41.034
Bye.

32:46.498 --> 32:48.667
Hello, Ted.

32:48.750 --> 32:53.421
Wish it was Ted. Don't forget
to set the alarm.

34:20.717 --> 34:22.636
Hello?

35:00.882 --> 35:02.842
No! Please, no!

35:02.926 --> 35:07.806
- No!

35:09.516 --> 35:12.519
Never said I was innocent

35:12.602 --> 35:15.897
I will burn in hell
for the things I've done to you

35:15.981 --> 35:18.942
Never said
I was anything good

35:23.405 --> 35:25.824
Everyone thinks that sororities
are just about blow jobs,

35:25.907 --> 35:29.995
- but it's not true.
- We only promote safe, condomed sex.

35:30.078 --> 35:32.789
See, we're about love,
respect and responsibility.

35:32.873 --> 35:35.083
Harmonica style
is okay, right?

35:35.166 --> 35:37.085
- Oh, yeah.
- Cocktail?

35:37.168 --> 35:39.254
What took you so long?

35:39.337 --> 35:41.673
And you know, Derek is
a Delta Lambda big brother.

35:41.756 --> 35:44.551
And we like to keep it
all in the family.

35:44.634 --> 35:48.054
Wow. You know, you girls have
really given me a lot to think about.

35:48.138 --> 35:50.056
Thanks.

35:50.140 --> 35:52.309
It's working.
It's working.

35:52.350 --> 35:55.103
- Hey, babe. You wanna dance?
- Oh, I'd love to...

35:55.187 --> 35:58.815
with that tall, wide-shouldered
fraternity boy.

35:58.899 --> 36:01.860
- Think you can arrange that?
- That hurts.

36:01.902 --> 36:06.156
The Empire Strikes Back. It
was a better story, improved effects.

36:06.198 --> 36:08.658
Not a sequel. It was part of a trilogy.
Completely planned.

36:08.700 --> 36:10.660
I like those
little furry things.

36:10.702 --> 36:12.662
They're Ewoks.
They blow.

36:12.704 --> 36:14.664
Hey.

36:14.706 --> 36:16.666
- How ya doin'?
- Good.

36:16.708 --> 36:19.669
- Twits being nice to you?
- Painfully nice.

36:19.711 --> 36:22.672
I take it you will not be pledging
Delta Lambda Zeta.

36:22.714 --> 36:25.217
I think not.

36:25.258 --> 36:27.844
- I'm crushed.
- Hey, guys.

36:27.928 --> 36:29.888
Something is up
at Omega Beta Zeta.

36:29.930 --> 36:32.682
- Police are everywhere.
- Hurry!

36:32.766 --> 36:36.019
Come on, let's go!

36:52.786 --> 36:54.746
- Way to break up the party!
- Shit!

36:54.788 --> 36:56.748
I should have brought
my drink.

37:04.214 --> 37:06.925
Death by blunt trauma,
and there's a double stabbing.

37:07.008 --> 37:09.678
So it's definitely
not suicide.

37:09.761 --> 37:11.721
Okay.
Thank you.

37:16.768 --> 37:18.895
Gale, hi. You're just getting here.
It's not good.

37:18.937 --> 37:21.064
It's a single victim:
Sorority girl.

37:21.147 --> 37:24.234
So- I gotta go.
I've got a deadline.

37:27.445 --> 37:31.283
- Joel, let's go.
- In-In a minute.

37:31.324 --> 37:33.827
It's happening again,
isn't it?

37:33.910 --> 37:35.829
You'd love that,
wouldn't you?

37:35.912 --> 37:38.874
- Please, stay back.

37:39.958 --> 37:42.335
Better hurry, Gale.
Might get scooped.

37:42.419 --> 37:44.337
Come on, I'm just trying
to get close enough...

37:44.421 --> 37:46.715
- to get a shot.
- Move it, Joel.

37:48.216 --> 37:52.429
Gale, I have to be honest with you.
I'm not cut out for this.

37:52.512 --> 37:56.516
I mean, I was brought here to do
an interview, not Faces of Death 14.

37:56.600 --> 37:58.685
Do not fuck with me.

38:11.156 --> 38:13.116
Come on.
Get your jacket.

38:13.158 --> 38:15.118
Let's get you home.

38:15.160 --> 38:17.120
Yeah.

38:48.026 --> 38:50.946
- You about ready?

38:56.034 --> 38:57.953
Almost.

39:02.165 --> 39:05.168
- Hello?
- Hello, Sidney.

39:05.210 --> 39:07.420
Remember me?

39:07.504 --> 39:12.509
- What do you want?
- I want you. It's show time.

39:12.551 --> 39:15.428
Then why don't you show your face,
you fucking coward.

39:15.512 --> 39:17.430
- My pleasure.

39:17.514 --> 39:19.266
Derek!

39:20.809 --> 39:23.728
- Sid? Sid?

39:24.813 --> 39:26.565
Derek!

39:26.648 --> 39:29.067
- Sid?

39:31.736 --> 39:33.321
Sid!

39:46.585 --> 39:48.545
- It's me. It's me.

39:48.587 --> 39:51.590
- You okay? You okay?
- Yeah. Yeah.

39:51.631 --> 39:53.717
No, Derek!
Don't!

39:53.800 --> 39:55.760
Sid!

39:55.802 --> 39:57.762
Dewey!

39:57.804 --> 39:59.764
- The killer's in there. And Derek.

40:15.071 --> 40:17.866
- You all right?
- He went that way.

40:17.949 --> 40:20.076
Sidney, he's in here!

40:24.789 --> 40:26.708
Is everything okay?

40:29.377 --> 40:33.298
He got me. He got me.

40:36.801 --> 40:38.762
- Now, apply pressure to it.
- Don't do that-

40:42.974 --> 40:45.393
The police are on their way.

40:54.903 --> 40:57.030
Thanks for your cooperation.

40:57.113 --> 40:59.282
Hallie, I'll be with you
in a few minutes, okay?

40:59.366 --> 41:01.701
Uh, no problem.

41:01.785 --> 41:05.914
That's the easiest interrogation
of my crime-filled life.

41:05.997 --> 41:08.959
I'm gonna go get a quick cup of coffee.
You want?

41:09.042 --> 41:11.419
No.

41:11.503 --> 41:13.421
You want some, Sid?

41:16.967 --> 41:19.177
How you doin'?
You all right?

41:19.261 --> 41:21.179
Not at all.

41:22.764 --> 41:25.183
You know, I knew
this was coming.

41:25.267 --> 41:29.604
- I knew this wasn't over.
- You are not alone, Sid.

41:29.688 --> 41:32.357
Okay?
We are all here for you.

41:32.440 --> 41:34.526
All right?
Whatever you need.

41:36.027 --> 41:39.197
- That poor girl.
- I know.

41:39.281 --> 41:41.366
It's crazy, but-

41:41.449 --> 41:45.287
- Derek could've been killed, you know.
- But he wasn't.

41:45.370 --> 41:50.250
He's fine.
He just needs to realize...

41:50.333 --> 41:52.711
the '90s is no time
to play hero.

41:52.794 --> 41:54.713
Why would anyone go back
in that house anyway?

41:59.259 --> 42:02.262
I went around to the back of the house
and ran into Sid there.

42:02.345 --> 42:05.390
That's when she told me the killer
was inside, so I went in to see.

42:05.473 --> 42:08.560
- You're lucky there's no nerve damage.

42:08.643 --> 42:11.188
You're gonna have
to take it easy though.

42:11.229 --> 42:15.317
- So then you went back inside the house?
- Yeah.

42:15.400 --> 42:18.236
No struggle? He just cut you
and ran away?

42:18.320 --> 42:22.657
- You're lucky he didn't kill you.
- Yeah, it's awfully convenient.

42:22.741 --> 42:26.703
- Say what?
- Nothing.

42:26.745 --> 42:28.788
It's just a shame
he got away so easily.

42:28.872 --> 42:31.541
It's just a shame
you got there too late,

42:31.583 --> 42:33.835
right after he disappeared.

42:38.924 --> 42:40.759
Yeah, it is.

43:00.278 --> 43:02.197
We got three victims.

43:02.280 --> 43:05.825
Maureen Evans,
Phil Stevens...

43:05.909 --> 43:08.703
and Cici Cooper.

43:08.787 --> 43:12.290
- Is Cici the girl's real name?
- Oh, uh, no.

43:12.374 --> 43:15.210
It's, uh, Casey.
Casey Cooper.

43:17.754 --> 43:20.423
As in Casey Becker?

43:20.465 --> 43:24.594
- Excuse me?
- She was a young victim in Woodsboro.

43:24.678 --> 43:28.640
As well as her boyfriend,
Steven Orth.

43:28.682 --> 43:30.767
As in Phil Stevens.

43:30.851 --> 43:34.646
Maureen Evans- Maureen Prescott.
That's Sidney's mother.

43:34.729 --> 43:37.691
Do you think someone's
trying to duplicate Woodsboro?

43:37.774 --> 43:40.151
It looks like it.

43:42.821 --> 43:44.990
I think you have a copycat
on your hands, Chief.

43:45.073 --> 43:47.534
Jesus Christ!

43:47.617 --> 43:49.578
What are you doing
to keep Sidney safe?

43:49.661 --> 43:52.873
I got my two best
detectives guarding her.

43:52.956 --> 43:56.334
Do these guys have to follow
you around everywhere?

43:56.418 --> 43:58.920
Oh. We're attached
at the hip.

43:59.004 --> 44:01.673
- How am I ever gonna get you alone?

44:01.756 --> 44:05.677
- You know, to be honest, Derek,

44:05.760 --> 44:09.139
I think it would probably be
in your best interest to...

44:09.181 --> 44:12.017
stay as far away
from me as possible.

44:13.852 --> 44:15.854
I hope that was an
off-the-cuff remark...

44:15.937 --> 44:19.191
that holds no
subtext whatsoever.

44:19.274 --> 44:23.195
No, actually.
I mean it.

44:26.364 --> 44:30.243
I mean, look at you.
You already got hurt.

44:30.327 --> 44:33.121
I don't want to see
that happen again.

44:33.205 --> 44:35.123
I'll take my chances.

44:35.207 --> 44:38.168
Derek, I'm serious.

44:38.251 --> 44:40.545
This is serious.

44:42.923 --> 44:46.885
You are concerned with my
personal well-being and...

44:48.595 --> 44:53.099
not with trusting me
or anything, right?

44:57.145 --> 44:59.064
Like I said, I just don't want
to see you get hurt.

44:59.147 --> 45:02.734
And I don't want
to see you get hurt.

45:02.817 --> 45:04.736
Okay, Sid?

45:16.623 --> 45:18.792
- Take care, Miss Weathers.
- All right.

45:21.586 --> 45:24.130
- Dewey.
- Chief.

45:25.382 --> 45:27.300
Hi.

45:27.384 --> 45:30.846
So, I'm heading over to admissions
to do some leg work. You game?

45:30.929 --> 45:33.515
I'm not here to write
a book, Miss Weathers.

45:33.598 --> 45:35.517
I'm here to help Sid.

45:37.561 --> 45:40.272
I want to help her, too.

45:40.355 --> 45:43.316
And help myself,
of course.

45:45.318 --> 45:49.573
Come on, Dewey. Smile just once.
Please?

45:51.408 --> 45:53.326
I'll smile when
I catch the killer.

45:56.913 --> 45:58.832
Gale, hi. So who
do you think did it?

45:58.915 --> 46:01.334
What about Sidney's father?
Has he been ruled out as a suspect?

46:01.418 --> 46:03.336
Well, he's supposedly out of the country
on business,

46:03.420 --> 46:05.338
but that sounds a little fishy,
don't you think?

46:05.422 --> 46:08.550
- I'm not here to do your job, Miss Salt.
- What about this ex-cop, Dewey?

46:08.633 --> 46:10.969
- It's kind of strange that he showed up.
- Yeah, what's he doing here?

46:11.052 --> 46:14.264
Dewey's a good guy,
unlike some of us.

46:16.349 --> 46:18.810
Really?

46:18.852 --> 46:21.438
Well, it just seems to me that
if the killer is repeating...

46:21.479 --> 46:23.523
what happened in Woodsboro,
it's quite possible that the killer...

46:23.607 --> 46:25.525
could be from Woodsboro.

46:25.609 --> 46:27.527
That's all.

46:29.404 --> 46:33.450
Derek, you think Sid will let me
interview her for my documentary?

46:33.491 --> 46:37.954
Oh, yeah. You know, she turned down
Primetime Live, 20/20 and Dateline.

46:38.038 --> 46:40.582
- But for you, yeah.
- Drop it.

46:40.665 --> 46:43.084
I've been thinking about
this whole murder thing.

46:43.168 --> 46:45.337
- Have they checked out Randy?
- What?

46:45.420 --> 46:48.632
I know he's an innocent victim the first
time around, but he's a little off.

46:48.715 --> 46:52.469
- You know what I'm saying?
- Come on. Randy? The guy's harmless.

46:52.511 --> 46:55.013
- That's what they said about Dahmer.
- Guys, keep it down.

46:55.096 --> 46:57.140
Come on.
What's up, Sid?

46:57.224 --> 47:00.101
- Hey, Sid.
- How's it goin'?

47:00.185 --> 47:02.187
Where are
the Secret Service guys?

47:02.270 --> 47:04.189
Uh, over there.

47:05.815 --> 47:07.776
And which one
is Kevin Costner?

47:07.859 --> 47:10.737
The one on the right
is Officer Richards.

47:10.820 --> 47:13.949
He is a Capricorn.
Divorced. Father of two.

47:14.032 --> 47:18.578
And the one on the left
is Officer Andrews. He is a Gemini.

47:18.662 --> 47:20.872
He's single,
but I think he's gay.

47:20.956 --> 47:23.416
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

47:23.500 --> 47:25.544
Derek?
Penny for your thoughts.

47:28.672 --> 47:32.676
"This morning, I woke up
with this feeling...

47:32.759 --> 47:35.720
I didn't know
how to deal with."

47:35.804 --> 47:39.432
And so I just
decided to myself

47:39.516 --> 47:42.018
I'd hide it to myself

47:42.102 --> 47:44.062
- What is he doing?

47:44.104 --> 47:47.190
Uh, Tom Cruise,
Top Gun, 1986.

47:47.232 --> 47:50.235
- Derek, don't.
- When you walked into the room

47:50.277 --> 47:52.571
- I think I love you
- Don't do this.

47:52.654 --> 47:56.825
I think I love you
Isn't that what life is made of

47:56.908 --> 48:00.412
And though
it worries me to say

48:00.495 --> 48:03.415
- I've never felt this way, hey

48:03.456 --> 48:07.836
I think I love you
So what am I so afraid of

48:07.919 --> 48:11.756
I'm afraid that I'm not sure of
A love there is no cure for

48:13.633 --> 48:16.970
I think I love you
Isn't that what life is made of

48:17.053 --> 48:19.264
- And though it worries me to say

48:19.347 --> 48:22.434
- I've never felt this way

48:22.517 --> 48:25.937
Believe me
You really don't have to worry

48:25.979 --> 48:28.231
I only wanna
make you happy

48:28.273 --> 48:30.483
And if you say
"Hey, go away"

48:30.567 --> 48:33.445
I will
But I think better still

48:33.528 --> 48:35.947
I better stick around
and love you

48:35.989 --> 48:39.367
Do you think I have a case
Let me ask you to your face

48:39.451 --> 48:42.621
Do you really love me
'Cause I think

48:42.704 --> 48:46.625
I love you

48:59.054 --> 49:01.890
Let's show
a little love, huh?

49:08.772 --> 49:10.690
Come on.
Come here, come here.

49:12.567 --> 49:16.947
Don't worry, Sid.
I know things are a little crazy.

49:18.657 --> 49:21.701
Isn't that a big
frat faux pas?

49:21.785 --> 49:23.745
Oh, yeah.
That is a big no-no.

49:23.828 --> 49:26.289
See, you're not supposed to give
your Greek letters to your girl...

49:26.373 --> 49:28.333
no shape, way or form.

49:28.375 --> 49:30.335
The brothers are gonna kick his ass,
but it's tradition.

49:30.377 --> 49:33.880
- It's tradition.
- It's good luck.

49:33.964 --> 49:36.007
It'll protect you.

49:50.647 --> 49:53.733
So, tell us about this part
you're getting rave reviews for.

49:53.817 --> 49:56.278
Well, I play this young girl,
Sidney Prescott,

49:56.361 --> 49:59.823
who discovers that her boyfriend
is this crazy serial killer...

49:59.906 --> 50:01.950
who also killed her mother
the year before that.

50:02.033 --> 50:04.119
So what kind of research
did you do for the part?

50:04.202 --> 50:07.330
I don't get it. They get
Tori Spelling to play Sid,

50:07.414 --> 50:09.875
and they cast Joe Blow Nobody
to play me.

50:09.958 --> 50:12.669
- At least you get David Schwimmer.

50:12.752 --> 50:14.838
I get the guy who drove
Jane Seymore's stagecoach...

50:14.880 --> 50:17.632
for one episode
of Doctor Quinn.

50:17.716 --> 50:20.927
This is Tori Spelling
starring in the new film Stab.

50:26.391 --> 50:29.477
Billy, you scared me.

50:29.561 --> 50:32.647
- What are you doing here?
- They let me go, Sid. I didn't do it.

50:32.731 --> 50:34.983
- I'm innocent.
- I know.

50:35.066 --> 50:37.736
- Please.
- Why won't you let me touch you?

50:39.779 --> 50:44.326
Look, I've been going through a lot
lately, Billy. And with my mom-

50:44.409 --> 50:48.371
Sid, I think you need
to just deal with that and move on.

50:48.455 --> 50:50.999
I mean, when my mom
left my dad, I accepted it.

50:51.082 --> 50:54.669
That's the way
the cookie crumbles. Moms leave.

50:54.753 --> 50:59.382
Yeah, your mom left town. She's not
buried in the cemetery somewhere.

50:59.466 --> 51:02.552
My mom's dead, and she's
never coming back. Ever.

51:05.931 --> 51:09.142
- Stupid.
- Ooh, I love scary movies.

51:09.226 --> 51:12.020
I'll wait for video. Okay,
let's get down to business.

51:12.103 --> 51:14.147
The way I see it,
someone's out to make a sequel.

51:14.231 --> 51:16.316
You know, cash in on all
the movie murder hoopla.

51:16.399 --> 51:19.194
So it's our job to observe
the rules of the sequel.

51:19.277 --> 51:21.863
Number one: The body count
is always bigger.

51:21.947 --> 51:26.409
Two: The death scenes are always much
more elaborate; more blood, more gore.

51:26.451 --> 51:29.371
Carnage candy. Your core audience
just expects it.

51:29.454 --> 51:33.458
And three: If you want your sequel
to become a franchise, never ever-

51:33.542 --> 51:35.794
How do we find the killer, Randy?
That's what I wanna know.

51:35.877 --> 51:38.421
Oh. Let's look
at the suspects.

51:38.505 --> 51:41.758
There's Derek, the obvious boyfriend.
Hello, Billy Loomis.

51:41.800 --> 51:44.177
The guy's premed, and his
pity-me surface wound...

51:44.261 --> 51:46.972
conveniently missed every major vein
and artery.

51:47.055 --> 51:50.392
- So you think it's Derek?
- Not so fast.

51:50.475 --> 51:52.811
Let's assume the killer,
or 'ers, has a half a brain.

51:52.894 --> 51:55.146
He's not a Nick At Night
rerun type of guy.

51:55.230 --> 51:57.148
He wants to break
some new ground.

51:57.232 --> 51:59.401
- Right? So forget the boyfriend.
- Right.

51:59.484 --> 52:01.903
- It's tired. Who else do we got?
- There's-

52:01.987 --> 52:04.823
Mickey, the freaky
Tarantino film student.

52:06.741 --> 52:10.203
But if he's a suspect, so am I.
So, let's move on.

52:10.287 --> 52:12.205
Whoa, wait a-
Let's not move on.

52:12.289 --> 52:14.833
Maybe you are a suspect.

52:14.916 --> 52:17.627
Well, if I'm a suspect,
you're a suspect.

52:19.629 --> 52:22.716
You have a point.

52:22.799 --> 52:25.343
Okay, let's move on to-

52:25.427 --> 52:27.554
- Hallie.
- Sid's roommate?

52:27.637 --> 52:30.682
- Uh-huh. - Serial killers
are typically white males.

52:30.765 --> 52:34.394
That's why it's perfect. It's sort of
against the rules, but not really.

52:34.477 --> 52:37.397
Mrs. Voorhees was
a terrific serial killer.

52:37.480 --> 52:39.733
And there's always room
for Candyman's daughter.

52:39.816 --> 52:42.569
She's sweet. She's deadly.
She's bad for your teeth.

52:45.697 --> 52:48.366
Come on, Randy.
These kids are your friends.

52:48.450 --> 52:50.785
Who do you think's
the killer?

52:50.869 --> 52:54.164
- How about Gale Weathers?
- Gale? A killer?

52:54.247 --> 52:58.293
- Why not?
- Well, she is vicious enough.

52:58.376 --> 53:00.754
- She's an opportunist.
- Yeah.

53:00.837 --> 53:03.173
Isn't it conceivable
she's planning her next book?

53:03.215 --> 53:06.760
That's what reporters do, Dewey.
They stage the news.

53:06.843 --> 53:09.763
No. Gale's a lot of things,
but Gale's not a killer.

53:09.846 --> 53:12.599
- Just because you're sweet on her-
- No, I'm not.

53:12.682 --> 53:14.684
Please, this is me talking.
Randy,

53:14.768 --> 53:17.145
the unrequited love-slave
of Sidney Prescott.

53:17.229 --> 53:19.814
I know all
about obsession...

53:19.898 --> 53:21.816
and pain.

53:21.900 --> 53:25.278
- You've got your love scar to prove it.
- And so do you.

53:25.362 --> 53:28.323
And what's with that limp anyway,
'cause you were stabbed in the back.

53:28.406 --> 53:31.952
Severed nerve.
Look, Gale's no killer.

53:33.078 --> 53:35.705
Okay, okay.
Whatever you say.

53:35.747 --> 53:38.959
But if she's not a killer,
she's a target.

53:41.086 --> 53:43.129
Joel, let's get
some establishing shots.

53:43.213 --> 53:45.215
Um, Gale,
can we talk for a sec?

53:45.257 --> 53:47.634
- What is it?
- Look, I'm a little confused here.

53:47.717 --> 53:49.761
I mean, with your
given track record,

53:49.845 --> 53:51.972
why would you wanna be here
when the killer strikes again?

53:52.055 --> 53:55.433
I mean, granted, I should've read
your book before I took this job.

53:55.475 --> 53:57.644
But I'm reading it now,
and- Whoo!

53:57.727 --> 53:59.688
I read what happened
to your last cameraman.

53:59.771 --> 54:02.440
The guy got gutted.
Now, me,

54:02.524 --> 54:04.568
I'm gonna do what any
rational human being would do,

54:04.651 --> 54:06.611
which is get the fuck
out of here.

54:06.653 --> 54:08.905
First of all, he wasn't gutted.
I made that up.

54:08.989 --> 54:10.949
His throat was slashed.

54:10.991 --> 54:13.076
What are you-
Gale, gutted, slashed,

54:13.159 --> 54:15.120
the guy ain't in
the union no more.

54:15.161 --> 54:17.122
It's a job, Joel.

54:17.163 --> 54:19.416
And like every job,
there's a few drawbacks.

54:19.499 --> 54:23.044
But you're a professional cameraman.
You've got to act like one.

54:23.128 --> 54:25.547
Yeah, but I wanna report the news.
I don't wanna be the news.

54:25.630 --> 54:28.383
Besides, brothers don't last long
in situations like this.

54:28.466 --> 54:32.304
This is national television.
Think about it.

54:32.387 --> 54:34.306
This is a big chance
for you.

54:34.389 --> 54:37.184
The story is monumental.
Don't you wanna be a part of that?

54:38.268 --> 54:40.020
Come on.

54:40.103 --> 54:43.565
I need you.
I cannot do this without you.

54:46.526 --> 54:48.486
Good.
Come on.

54:48.528 --> 54:51.865
- Let's get some work done.
- Yeah, let's go get killed.

54:55.035 --> 54:58.830
We've been through this before. You know what
I think about your potential as an actress.

54:58.997 --> 55:00.790
I know.
I know.

55:00.957 --> 55:03.960
It-It's just that with,
um, the murders...

55:04.002 --> 55:07.422
and the movie
and my life-

55:07.464 --> 55:10.217
I do know how difficult
it is for you.

55:11.885 --> 55:14.638
Gus, I-I just-
I don't think I can do it.

55:14.763 --> 55:18.600
The battle for the soul is
fought in the forum of art.

55:18.683 --> 55:22.020
You're a fighter, Sid. That's why you're
here. That's why this is your major.

55:22.103 --> 55:24.439
- Yeah, I'm a fighter.
- I didn't hear that.

55:26.149 --> 55:29.027
- I'm a fighter.
- I don't believe you.

55:31.571 --> 55:33.532
I don't.

55:35.367 --> 55:38.036
I'm a fighter.

55:38.119 --> 55:40.038
Okay.

55:42.123 --> 55:45.335
So, at the risk of sounding
like a college drama teacher,

55:45.377 --> 55:48.380
if you've got pain around
this kind of material, use it.

55:48.421 --> 55:51.049
This is your role, Sid.

55:51.132 --> 55:54.553
Cassandra is one of the great tragic
visionaries of literature.

55:54.636 --> 55:58.223
She saw it all coming.
The wars,

55:58.306 --> 56:01.393
the murder,
the madness.

56:03.144 --> 56:05.856
She knew
she was cursed.

56:05.939 --> 56:08.984
It was her fate,
and she embraced it.

56:09.067 --> 56:13.822
None of us can avoid our fate,
but as an artist...

56:13.905 --> 56:16.533
you can honestly face it...

56:16.575 --> 56:18.535
and fight it.

56:22.414 --> 56:25.375
- You're good.
- There's no understudy. I'm desperate.

56:29.671 --> 56:31.673
You can do this.

56:36.928 --> 56:40.098
Okay, everybody. Gather around.
Third Act, one last time.

56:40.182 --> 56:43.018
Cue the music.

56:55.488 --> 56:59.701
All behold the dreaded
fate of Troy...

56:59.784 --> 57:04.789
that once stood proud and light
upon the hills of Sparta!

57:04.873 --> 57:09.544
Now shrouded in
the deathly smoke of ruin,

57:09.628 --> 57:13.632
her royal children
pitched from her walls,

57:13.715 --> 57:18.470
her people driven
through her ruins.

57:18.553 --> 57:23.975
And now alone in
fate's cruel isolation...

57:24.017 --> 57:26.478
stands Cassandra,

57:26.561 --> 57:30.774
her kingdom,
family and friends...

57:30.815 --> 57:33.693
driven to the wind.

57:35.195 --> 57:39.950
- No crime against gods or man...

57:39.991 --> 57:41.910
have I committed,

57:41.993 --> 57:45.163
saith to speak
the truth.

57:45.247 --> 57:49.626
And each hideous vision
born from my mind...

57:49.668 --> 57:52.629
has come to pass.

57:52.671 --> 57:55.674
Troy has fallen,

57:55.715 --> 57:59.469
not by my hand
or wish,

58:00.637 --> 58:02.556
but as I foresaw.

58:06.935 --> 58:10.397
So now,
fate's vengeful eye...

58:10.480 --> 58:12.440
is fixed...

58:14.359 --> 58:17.779
on me.

58:17.863 --> 58:21.324
Tell us, O Cassandra,
where has the sweetness...

58:21.366 --> 58:23.493
of life gone?

58:23.535 --> 58:27.289
What stays fate's hand
from striking now at thee?

58:27.372 --> 58:29.708
What stays fate's hand
from thee?

58:29.791 --> 58:32.377
What stays fate's hand
from thee?

58:32.460 --> 58:34.379
What stays fate's hand
from thee?

58:34.462 --> 58:37.007
What stays fate's hand
from thee?

58:57.736 --> 59:02.157
All right, hold it.
Hold it!

59:04.326 --> 59:07.162
Everyone, take five.

59:21.551 --> 59:24.429
Sidney?

59:36.024 --> 59:39.778
Sid.
Your escort has arrived.

59:39.861 --> 59:42.531
- Derek, how long have you been here?
- I just got here.

59:42.614 --> 59:45.450
- Is everything okay? What's goin' on?
- What happened to Mickey?

59:45.534 --> 59:48.453
We swapped. He had to edit.
You get me instead. What happened?

59:48.537 --> 59:51.414
Derek, don't.

59:53.500 --> 59:57.212
Don't. I-I just need to be alone
right now, okay?

59:59.631 --> 01:00:02.133
Being alone is not
the answer, Sid.

01:00:02.217 --> 01:00:06.346
Yeah, well,
I think it is.

01:00:06.429 --> 01:00:09.224
I need some distance.

01:00:12.811 --> 01:00:14.729
Well, do I
get a say in this?

01:00:17.190 --> 01:00:19.150
No.

01:00:24.030 --> 01:00:28.118
I guess I'm supposed
to be... understanding.

01:00:29.411 --> 01:00:32.747
Yeah.

01:00:37.669 --> 01:00:39.588
You got it.

01:00:47.512 --> 01:00:50.640
All right. Let's just assume the killer
is repeating Woodsboro-

01:00:50.724 --> 01:00:52.809
- Yes?

01:00:52.851 --> 01:00:55.103
- I have Bob calling.
- I'll have to call you back.

01:00:55.187 --> 01:00:57.898
That doesn't
explain Sidney's attack.

01:00:57.981 --> 01:01:00.483
Sidney wasn't killed
in Woodsboro.

01:01:00.567 --> 01:01:02.652
Wasn't for
a lack of trying.

01:01:02.736 --> 01:01:05.071
The killer's trying
to finish what was started.

01:01:05.155 --> 01:01:07.282
- Sid's under protection, right?
- Yeah.

01:01:07.365 --> 01:01:09.618
- What?

01:01:09.701 --> 01:01:12.204
- Bob really needs to talk to you-
- Tell Bob I'll call him back.

01:01:12.287 --> 01:01:15.707
- When'd she start smoking?
- Ever since those nude pictures on the internet.

01:01:15.790 --> 01:01:17.959
It was just my head.
It was Jennifer Aniston's body.

01:01:18.043 --> 01:01:20.045
Anyway, you're
forgetting something.

01:01:20.128 --> 01:01:22.839
In Woodsboro, there were more victims
before the homestretch-

01:01:22.881 --> 01:01:25.217
Tatum, my cameraman,
Himbry-

01:01:25.300 --> 01:01:29.721
Time out! I don't need to be hearing
about no dead cameramen, all right?

