- Whoo!

01:24:53.341 --> 01:24:55.426
This is so romantic.

01:24:55.468 --> 01:24:57.595
- And so Greek!

01:25:03.434 --> 01:25:08.106
I was in the wrong place
But it must have been the right time

01:25:08.189 --> 01:25:12.276
I was in the right place
But it must have been the wrong song

01:25:12.360 --> 01:25:17.115
I was in the right vein
But it seemed like the wrong arm

01:25:17.198 --> 01:25:20.993
I was in the right world
But it seemed like wrong, wrong, wrong

01:25:21.119 --> 01:25:24.789
- Wrong song
- Who do you love, baby?

01:25:24.872 --> 01:25:28.793
- Sidney.
- Did you say

01:25:28.835 --> 01:25:31.045
No, I said Sidney!

01:25:53.050 --> 01:25:55.386
So, where are you
taking us, anyway?

01:25:55.469 --> 01:25:58.305
If we tell you,
we'll have to kill you.

01:25:59.557 --> 01:26:01.517
Don't ask; don't tell.

01:26:32.089 --> 01:26:33.841
Help me!

01:26:35.009 --> 01:26:37.761
Oh, my God!

01:26:38.355 --> 01:26:40.774
Outta the car,
you fucker!

01:26:48.031 --> 01:26:50.951
Get down back there!
Come on, you son-of-a-bitch!

01:26:50.992 --> 01:26:52.953
I'll blow your
fuckin' head-

01:27:32.242 --> 01:27:36.746
- Is he dead?
- I don't think so.

01:27:38.707 --> 01:27:41.793
- He's still breathing.
- Oh!

01:27:45.422 --> 01:27:47.465
Oh, is he dead?

01:27:47.507 --> 01:27:50.260
Oh, God.
I think so.

01:27:57.267 --> 01:28:01.354
- How are you
supposed to get outta here?

01:28:09.946 --> 01:28:13.950
Hallie, it's the only way out.
Help me out.

01:28:17.537 --> 01:28:19.456
Come on.

01:28:46.316 --> 01:28:49.069
We're jammed up against
a pole.

01:28:52.113 --> 01:28:53.990
Oh, my God.

01:29:08.838 --> 01:29:10.966
Oh. Oh, my God.

01:29:13.176 --> 01:29:15.762
Come on, Sid.
Don't! Sid!

01:29:21.017 --> 01:29:23.770
God, I hate this shit.

01:29:26.189 --> 01:29:30.026
Oh, my God.
Don't do that again.

01:29:41.538 --> 01:29:43.623
Try the window.

01:29:58.388 --> 01:30:00.307
- Shit!
- Get me the fuck outta here, Sid.

01:30:00.390 --> 01:30:03.893
I can't. The door's jammed.
You have to go through the front.

01:30:03.977 --> 01:30:05.979
- Oh, no fuckin' way.
- Hallie, do it.

01:30:06.062 --> 01:30:09.816
Go on.
Hallie, go.

01:30:17.907 --> 01:30:19.826
Okay.

01:30:19.909 --> 01:30:23.663
Okay, that's right.
Shh.

01:30:24.998 --> 01:30:28.084
Okay.
Okay, that's good.

01:30:31.004 --> 01:30:33.506
Oh, right
through his eye.

01:30:33.590 --> 01:30:35.592
Come on.

01:30:35.675 --> 01:30:37.677
That's good. Easy. Easy.

01:30:37.761 --> 01:30:40.430
He's not gonna hurt you.

01:30:50.774 --> 01:30:53.068
Come on. Let's go.
Let's go.

01:30:55.862 --> 01:30:59.616
- Hallie.
- What?

01:30:59.699 --> 01:31:01.785
I wanna know
who it is.

01:31:01.868 --> 01:31:04.037
- Oh, no. Come on, Sid.
Please? Let's just go.

01:31:04.079 --> 01:31:06.539
Look, look.
Stupid people go back.

01:31:06.623 --> 01:31:09.793
Smart people run. We're smart people, so
we should just get the fuck outta here.

01:31:09.876 --> 01:31:12.212
Hallie, I'm sick
of running.

01:31:12.462 --> 01:31:15.381
- If we know who it is, then it's over.
- No, we can just get the police.

01:31:15.464 --> 01:31:18.550
And when we come back, he'll be gone.
It'll only take a minute.

01:31:18.633 --> 01:31:22.969
- I have to do this.
- Sid. No, Sid. Come back!

01:31:23.052 --> 01:31:27.055
Sid, come back.
Shit.

01:31:38.229 --> 01:31:40.897
- Oh, shit.
- What?

01:31:42.148 --> 01:31:45.567
- He's gone!
- What?

01:31:45.650 --> 01:31:47.985
- No!

01:32:14.232 --> 01:32:15.108
- Gale.

01:32:17.194 --> 01:32:18.000
Get away from me.

01:32:18.001 --> 01:32:20.673
This isn't what it looks like.

01:32:20.756 --> 01:32:24.341
I found Dewey. I tried to help him.
I- No, no. Gale, wait.

01:32:24.425 --> 01:32:26.594
Gale! Gale, wait!
Gale!

01:32:29.289 --> 01:32:30.165
Shit.

01:32:36.433 --> 01:32:38.054
- You can't miss the street-
- Help me!

01:32:38.089 --> 01:32:41.603
...curfew in full effect.
- Give me the goddamn phone!

01:32:41.686 --> 01:32:45.604
- Gale. I was right
in the middle of a story.

01:32:45.639 --> 01:32:48.691
- What's the matter?
- Operator, this is an emergency!

01:32:48.726 --> 01:32:50.936
- What's happening?
- The killer!

01:32:51.436 --> 01:32:53.021
Cotton Weary?

01:33:41.736 --> 01:33:42.612
Hello?

01:33:47.075 --> 01:33:47.951
Gus?

01:33:53.748 --> 01:33:54.583
Hello?

01:34:00.881 --> 01:34:01.840
Hello?

01:34:13.143 --> 01:34:14.060
Hello?

01:35:12.294 --> 01:35:14.297
Derek?

01:35:14.379 --> 01:35:17.718
Derek!
Oh, God.

01:35:17.801 --> 01:35:21.638
Thank you. Thank God, Sid. Thought I was
gonna be up there till opening night.

01:35:21.722 --> 01:35:24.558
- Shit! Who tied these?
We gotta get outta here.

01:35:24.641 --> 01:35:28.481
- He's out there. He killed Hallie.
- What are you talking about?

01:35:28.564 --> 01:35:31.151
- The killer! He's here.
- Where?

01:35:31.233 --> 01:35:34.487
Right here.

01:35:34.570 --> 01:35:37.406
- You're fast, Sid.
- Get me down. Hurry!

01:35:37.490 --> 01:35:41.997
I wouldn't do that if I were you.
You really wanna trust your boyfriend?

01:35:42.080 --> 01:35:45.833
Don't you know history repeats itself?

01:35:45.917 --> 01:35:47.836
Hmm, Sid?

01:35:55.094 --> 01:35:57.597
Mickey.

01:35:57.680 --> 01:36:00.936
Surprise, Sidney.

01:36:01.019 --> 01:36:05.774
- What the fuck?
- Since Derek, here,

01:36:05.857 --> 01:36:09.361
I been on my own
all fuckin' night.

01:36:09.444 --> 01:36:12.115
- Thanks a lot, partner.
- You motherfucker!

01:36:12.199 --> 01:36:14.701
Sid, he's crazy.
You know me better than that.

01:36:14.785 --> 01:36:19.373
Come on, Sid.
I gotta have a partner.

01:36:19.456 --> 01:36:22.211
I couldn't have possibly
done this alone.

01:36:22.294 --> 01:36:24.630
- God, Derek.
- Sid.

01:36:24.713 --> 01:36:28.217
Oh, no, Sid. Sid.
No, no, no, no.

01:36:28.300 --> 01:36:30.803
It's okay, Derek.
We got her.

01:36:30.888 --> 01:36:33.307
You-
Sid, he's lying!

01:36:33.391 --> 01:36:36.727
Sid! Sid!
Untie me.

01:36:36.811 --> 01:36:39.564
- Sid, untie me.
- Hmm?

01:36:39.647 --> 01:36:41.568
Boyfriend. Killer.
Boyfriend. Killer.

01:36:41.651 --> 01:36:44.821
Sid, the man is lying!
Untie me. Sid.

01:36:44.904 --> 01:36:47.824
Untie me.
Untie me.

01:36:47.907 --> 01:36:51.913
What do you think, Derek?
Sidney experiencing some deja vu?

01:36:51.998 --> 01:36:55.084
No. No. I am gonna
fuckin' kill you!

01:36:55.168 --> 01:36:58.587
Fuckin' kill you!
You are dead! Dead!

01:36:58.670 --> 01:37:01.673
- Derek.

01:37:01.756 --> 01:37:03.927
- Sid. - Derek.

01:37:08.515 --> 01:37:10.434
I'm sorry.

01:37:11.853 --> 01:37:14.608
I never...

01:37:14.691 --> 01:37:18.110
would've...
hurt you.

01:37:18.194 --> 01:37:20.530
Never.

01:37:32.627 --> 01:37:35.381
You should really deal with
your trust issues, Sid.

01:37:35.465 --> 01:37:39.135
I mean, poor Derek. He's completely
innocent. And such a nice boy too.

01:37:39.219 --> 01:37:43.473
He's bright and funny and
handsome. Decent singing voice.

01:37:43.556 --> 01:37:46.811
This was just the kind of boy
you'd like to take home to Mom.

01:37:46.895 --> 01:37:49.314
- If you had a mom.
- Fuck you!

01:37:49.397 --> 01:37:52.400
Oh! So vulgar. Did Billy
let you talk to him this way?

01:37:52.484 --> 01:37:55.155
Billy was a sick fuck,
just like you.

01:37:55.239 --> 01:37:58.075
No. Billy was a sick fuck
who tried to get away with it.

01:37:58.158 --> 01:38:00.911
Mickey is a sick fuck
who wants to get caught. Yeah!

01:38:00.994 --> 01:38:04.331
See, I've got my whole defense
planned out.

01:38:04.414 --> 01:38:07.002
I'm gonna blame
the movies.

01:38:07.086 --> 01:38:09.755
Pretty cool, huh?
It hasn't been done before.

01:38:09.839 --> 01:38:13.343
You see, this is just the beginning,
a prelude to the trial.

01:38:13.426 --> 01:38:16.848
That's where the real fun is 'cause
these days it's all about the trial.

01:38:16.931 --> 01:38:20.351
Can't you see it? The effects
of cinema violence on society.

01:38:20.434 --> 01:38:23.187
I'll get Dershovitz
or Cochran to represent me.

01:38:23.271 --> 01:38:25.606
Bob Dole on the witness stand
in my defense.

01:38:25.690 --> 01:38:28.027
Hell, the Christian Coalition'll
pay my legal fees.

01:38:28.111 --> 01:38:31.364
It's airtight, Sid.

01:38:31.447 --> 01:38:34.200
I'm an innocent victim.

01:38:34.284 --> 01:38:37.372
- You're a psychotic.
- Yeah, well. Shh.

01:38:37.455 --> 01:38:39.374
That'll be our little secret.

01:38:39.457 --> 01:38:43.545
'Cause people love a good trial.
It's like theater. They're dyin' for it.

01:38:43.628 --> 01:38:47.051
And I've worked hard
to give the audience what they want.

01:38:47.135 --> 01:38:50.637
That's what Billy was good at.
He knew... it's all about...

01:38:50.672 --> 01:38:52.472
- execution.
- Yeah?

01:38:52.556 --> 01:38:56.560
Well, you're forgetting
one thing about Billy Loomis.

01:38:56.643 --> 01:38:59.315
What's that?

01:38:59.398 --> 01:39:01.318
I fucking killed him.

01:39:01.401 --> 01:39:03.819
You piece of shit!

01:39:29.684 --> 01:39:31.603
Sid.

01:39:33.522 --> 01:39:36.107
You got a Linda Hamilton
thing going.

01:39:36.191 --> 01:39:39.110
No, no. It's nice.
I like it.

01:39:39.194 --> 01:39:42.699
Now, who's doin' that?

01:39:42.783 --> 01:39:47.204
Could that be... the mystery guest
waiting in the wings?

01:39:47.287 --> 01:39:49.875
Told ya I had a partner.

01:39:49.959 --> 01:39:51.962
Surprise cameo
just for you.

01:39:56.382 --> 01:39:58.801
Gale.

01:40:08.480 --> 01:40:11.569
Mrs. Loomis?

01:40:11.652 --> 01:40:15.989
- What?
- Billy's mother!

01:40:16.072 --> 01:40:19.492
Nice twist, huh?
Didn't see it comin', did ya?

01:40:20.493 --> 01:40:22.463
Jesus.

01:40:22.498 --> 01:40:25.501
It can't be. I've-
I've seen pictures of you.

01:40:25.585 --> 01:40:27.836
This is 60 pounds
and a lot of work later.

01:40:27.919 --> 01:40:30.672
It's called a make-over.
You should try it.

01:40:30.755 --> 01:40:34.177
Look a little tired
yourself there, Gale.

01:40:34.261 --> 01:40:37.180
- So you two are in this together?
- Yeah, well.

01:40:37.264 --> 01:40:42.019
Had to have financing.
Tuition's expensive.

01:40:42.105 --> 01:40:46.859
Deb, there- my backer. We met on the
Internet. Psycho Web site. Classifieds.

01:40:46.942 --> 01:40:51.280
There's only an estimated
97 active serial killers in the country.

01:40:51.363 --> 01:40:55.036
So Mickey, here, was quite a find.
Definitely one on the way up.

01:40:55.119 --> 01:40:59.041
- All he needed was a little
guidance and nurturing.

01:40:59.124 --> 01:41:01.877
Told you it was gonna work.
Wait till the trial!

01:41:01.960 --> 01:41:03.880
It is gonna rock!

01:41:03.963 --> 01:41:07.384
Oh, Mickey.
There's not gonna be a trial.

01:41:14.309 --> 01:41:16.561
- Gale!

01:41:29.576 --> 01:41:31.411
Two birds, one stone.

01:41:33.247 --> 01:41:37.586
Oh, Mickey was a good boy, but, my God,
that whole blame the movies motive.

01:41:37.670 --> 01:41:39.755
Did you buy that
for one second?

01:41:39.838 --> 01:41:42.925
Poor boy was completely
out of his mind.

01:41:43.008 --> 01:41:46.347
- And you're not?
- No. I'm very sane.

01:41:46.430 --> 01:41:49.934
My motive isn't
as '90s as Mickey's.

01:41:50.017 --> 01:41:53.354
Mine is just
good old fashioned revenge.

01:41:53.437 --> 01:41:56.276
You killed my son!

01:41:56.359 --> 01:42:00.113
And now I kill you. And I can't think
of anything more rational.

01:42:00.196 --> 01:42:02.949
You're never gonna
get away with this.

01:42:03.032 --> 01:42:05.368
Of course I will.

01:42:05.451 --> 01:42:07.706
Everything's traceable
back to Mickey.

01:42:07.789 --> 01:42:10.792
Including the cop gun he used
to kill everybody.

01:42:10.876 --> 01:42:12.961
But let's just suppose
that you...

01:42:13.044 --> 01:42:15.630
had gotten hold
of the other cop's gun.

01:42:15.714 --> 01:42:19.136
And you chased Mickey. And there was
a big shoot-out and a big scuffle.

01:42:19.219 --> 01:42:23.141
And you shot Mickey,
killed Mickey dead.

01:42:24.975 --> 01:42:29.481
But not before he got off
one shot at you.

01:42:29.565 --> 01:42:33.152
Okay. So, have I
covered everything?

01:42:33.235 --> 01:42:35.821
Are there any questions, any comments?
You know what, though?

01:42:35.905 --> 01:42:38.826
Who give a flyin' fuck
anyway?

01:42:38.910 --> 01:42:43.664
Let 'em try and track down
the second possible killer.

01:42:43.699 --> 01:42:47.001
You're as crazy
as your son was.

01:42:47.084 --> 01:42:50.340
What did you just say?

01:42:50.423 --> 01:42:55.178
Was that a negative, disparaging
remark about my son? About my Billy?

01:42:55.261 --> 01:42:57.347
No, Billy was a good boy.

01:42:57.430 --> 01:42:59.852
Billy was perfect.
You did a bang up job, Mrs. Loomis.

01:42:59.936 --> 01:43:03.104
It's not wise to patronize
a woman with a gun, Sidney.

01:43:03.188 --> 01:43:06.858
Randy spoke poorly of Billy,
and I got a little knife happy.

01:43:06.942 --> 01:43:09.363
I was a good mother.

01:43:09.446 --> 01:43:13.116
You know what
makes me sick?

01:43:13.200 --> 01:43:15.953
I'm sick to death of people saying
that it's all the parent's fault.

01:43:16.036 --> 01:43:18.622
That it all starts with the family.
You wanna blame someone?

01:43:18.705 --> 01:43:20.793
Why don't you blame
your mother?

01:43:20.876 --> 01:43:24.380
She's the one who stole my husband
and broke up my family.

01:43:24.463 --> 01:43:28.050
And then you took my son!

01:43:29.637 --> 01:43:32.557
You don't know what it is
to be a mother.

01:43:32.640 --> 01:43:37.061
To raise a child and teach him...
and guide him-

01:43:37.144 --> 01:43:39.695
And abandon him.

01:43:39.730 --> 01:43:41.986
Isn't Mickey
supposed to be dead?

01:46:20.173 --> 01:46:22.675
Don't you fuckin' move!

01:46:22.759 --> 01:46:25.511
- Goddammit!
- Cotton.

01:46:25.595 --> 01:46:28.934
Okay, okay, okay.
Everybody slow down.

01:46:29.017 --> 01:46:32.437
I have had
a very, very bad day,

01:46:32.520 --> 01:46:37.108
and I would like to know exactly
what the fuck is going on here?

01:46:37.192 --> 01:46:39.780
- Sidney?
- Cotton, meet Billy Loomis' mother.

01:46:39.863 --> 01:46:41.782
She's the killer.

01:46:41.865 --> 01:46:43.784
What?

01:46:46.955 --> 01:46:49.375
- Then who's that?
- The other killer.

01:46:49.458 --> 01:46:53.796
- Mickey.
- Okay.

01:46:53.879 --> 01:46:56.382
- Look, Cotton-
- Shut up.

01:46:56.465 --> 01:46:59.470
So. Hi.

01:47:01.139 --> 01:47:03.809
You're, uh,
not Debbie Salt, are you?

01:47:03.892 --> 01:47:06.645
You're not with
the Post Telegraph.

01:47:06.728 --> 01:47:09.483
No, but I can still
help you, Cotton.

01:47:09.566 --> 01:47:11.901
Ah-ah-ah!

01:47:11.985 --> 01:47:14.118
You don't need her.
Let me kill her!

01:47:14.153 --> 01:47:18.324
As long as she's alive,
you're never gonna be the lead story.

01:47:18.359 --> 01:47:20.663
That's what you really want,
isn't it, Cotton?

01:47:20.746 --> 01:47:23.081
If you really wanna be
in the spotlight,

01:47:23.164 --> 01:47:26.501
just let me kill her...
right now.

01:47:26.584 --> 01:47:29.921
Then you're the only survivor.
You're the star!

01:47:32.342 --> 01:47:36.144
She sent you to prison
for a year!

01:47:36.179 --> 01:47:39.516
Personally, I think
it's rather poetic.

01:47:46.609 --> 01:47:50.362
No. No, Cotton,
don't you listen to her.

01:47:50.446 --> 01:47:53.284
Well- Well-

01:47:53.367 --> 01:47:55.870
It's, uh, quite a predicament
you're in, Sid.

01:47:55.953 --> 01:47:59.540
- Cotton-
- I mean, she makes a good point.

01:47:59.624 --> 01:48:01.709
Let me think about this.

01:48:01.794 --> 01:48:03.880
Maybe you should too.

01:48:03.963 --> 01:48:07.133
Betcha that Diane Sawyer interview's
lookin' real good right about now.

01:48:10.970 --> 01:48:13.391
Huh?

01:48:23.570 --> 01:48:25.906
Consider it done.

01:48:46.180 --> 01:48:48.099
Wow.

01:48:48.182 --> 01:48:51.102
That... was intense.

01:49:03.116 --> 01:49:05.120
Hey, Sidney, uh-

01:49:05.203 --> 01:49:09.124
Look, I want you to know that I would
never, ever do anything to hurt you.

01:49:09.159 --> 01:49:12.043
Cotton, give me the gun.

01:49:15.132 --> 01:49:19.219
Yeah. Okay. Sure.
Take it.

01:49:19.303 --> 01:49:22.604
Hey, Sid, we should talk about
exactly what happened here.

01:49:22.639 --> 01:49:26.145
You know- I mean, get our stories
straight for the press statement.

01:49:26.228 --> 01:49:28.314
- Oh, shit!

01:49:28.397 --> 01:49:31.483
- Cotton.
- Could somebody get me outta here?

01:49:31.567 --> 01:49:33.986
Gale!
Are you all right?

01:49:34.069 --> 01:49:35.990
I been shot.
Of course not.

01:49:36.073 --> 01:49:38.624
- Help!
- Give me your hand, Gale.

01:49:38.659 --> 01:49:41.329
Jesus, Gale,
you scared the crap outta me.

01:49:41.412 --> 01:49:43.831
- Isn't anybody else
down there, is there?

01:49:43.914 --> 01:49:47.003
So much for reporting
from the trenches, huh?

01:49:47.086 --> 01:49:50.840
- Shut up, Cotton.
- How bad is it?

01:49:50.875 --> 01:49:53.259
Just bounced off my ribs.

01:49:53.343 --> 01:49:55.678
Geez, Gale, you got
more lives than a cat.

01:50:03.021 --> 01:50:06.441
Give me one of those.

01:50:06.524 --> 01:50:08.612
Is she dead?

01:50:08.695 --> 01:50:11.783
I don't know.
They always come back.

01:50:23.879 --> 01:50:25.798
Whoa!

01:50:41.317 --> 01:50:43.486
Just in case.

01:50:52.998 --> 01:50:55.291
- That about wraps it up, Chief.
- Okay, Frank.

01:50:55.326 --> 01:50:57.585
Take it easy.
You got a couple broken ribs.

01:50:57.669 --> 01:50:59.756
- Greg, I'm okay.
- Sure.

